      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Geographical Society of ¶ AUSTRALASIA. ¶ INSTITUTED 1883 ¶ NEW SOUTH WALES BRANCH. ¶ Sydney ¶  11 May  ¶ 188 ¶ 8...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.05.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Theodore Bevan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A38 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Geographical Society of</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">AUSTRALASIA.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">INSTITUTED 1883</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">NEW SOUTH WALES BRANCH.</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">Sydney</seg> 11 May <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">188</seg>8</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I duly received, my dear Baron, your valued and interesting letter and have to thank you for explaining the principle which your Geographic Council had in view in phrasing its resolution.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. See T. Bevan to M, 4 May 1888, and M to A. Macdonald, 7 May 1888.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One difficulty I have is not being able to get about as much as I should like: as that would enable me to explain a good many details personally to you; also to ask your experienced advice in advance on a good many points.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Next week I expect to have to pay a visit to some friends on the Clarence river,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> and after that I am uncertain as yet whether I may not have to make a short journey to England.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the meanwhile any letters, papers etc will be duly forwarded me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In my last expedition the only man amongst my employés who ranked above a common seaman or mechanic was Mr Hemmy who was paid by the Queensland Government £1 per day &amp; expenses from the time he left Brisbane.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Hemmy's report, included in Bevan (1888).</p>
               </note> All the other few employés whether black or white were paid extra wages by me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your suggestion about the various Branches of the Geographical Society joining in a united recommendation is a very valuable one if they could be got to do so.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Unfortunately I have noticed in Brisbane a sentiment not of friendship towards the Sydney Society and with the South Australian Branch I am quite unacquainted.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Theodore Bevan</p>
         </div>
      </body>
